BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1btssK-YxZixTxdrrmKvT
SUMMARY:Liz Cooper w/ Wes Parker
DTSTAMP:20260315T014747Z
DTSTART:20260326T030000Z
DESCRIPTION:Advance: $20 ($26.27 after fees)\n\nDay of: $25 ($31.42 after f
	ees)\n\nPlease note\, the Sunset Tavern is a strictly 21+ bar and venue an
	d does not accept vertical ID’s for entry.\n\nLiz Cooper:\n\nThe thing abo
	ut finding yourself is there's always another corner to turn. The Vermont-
	based singer/songwriter Liz Cooper made her third album during a period of
	 intense self-discovery and reinvention. She moved to New York for the fir
	st time\, weathered a pandemic\, came out to herself after falling in love
	 with a friend\, and experienced her first queer relationship and breakup\
	, all in the course of a few years. New Day marks both a personal and a mu
	sical revolution for Cooper – a plunge into psychedelic pop depths and a f
	ullhearted reflection of a whirlwind chapter in her life. These songs scin
	tillate with the kind of self-confidence that only beams through after you
	've aimed a sharp gaze inward and realized that whatever you see will alwa
	ys keep darting ahead of you.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/h78f204a871c\n\nFrom
	 Sunset Tavern
URL:https://link.dice.fm/h78f204a871c
LOCATION:5433 Ballard Avenue Northwest\, Seattle\, Washington 98107\, Unite
	d States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:sunset-tavern
CATEGORIES:Sunset Tavern
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
